## Repository Structure
See `STRUCTURE.md` for the full file tree (auto-updated every 10 commits).

This project is organized by the Five Tenets: Reproducibility, Correctness, Legibility, Observability, Security.

- `src/` — Reusable library and tooling code (functions always here, never in scripts/)
- `scripts/` — Pipeline steps (numbered, sequential). Orchestrators (Makefile, dvc.yaml, _targets.R) nest here visually.
- `outputs/` — Reports and visuals
- `reproducibility/` — Docker, environment configs, infrastructure
- `correctness/` — Tests, hooks
- `observability/` — Logging, monitoring, runbooks
- `security/` — Secrets (.gitignored), permissions, audit
- `legibility/` — Style guide, conventions, ADRs, architecture docs

## Development Commands
Run `make help` to see all available targets. Key ones:
- `make setup` — First-time project setup
- `make check` — Run all quality checks (lint + test)
- `make lint` — Run linter
- `make format` — Run formatter
- `make test` — Run test suite

## Conventions
- Scripts are numerically prefixed: `01_extract`, `02_transform`, etc.
- Every function must have tests in `correctness/tests/`
- Commit messages follow conventional commits format
- See `legibility/conventions.md` for full details
